               <p>DAVID BALLINGHALL. I am a <rs id="t18250407-177-viclabel964" type="occupation">journeyman tailor</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18250407-177-victim946 t18250407-177-viclabel964"></join>; and live at <placeName id="t18250407-177-crimeloc965">No. 8, Hewit's-court, Strand</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18250407-177-crimeloc965" type="placeName" value="No. 8, Hewit's-court, Strand"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18250407-177-crimeloc965" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18250407-177-off962 t18250407-177-crimeloc965"></join>. On Easter Monday I went out about ten o'clock in the morning, and returned about eight, and my coat was gone - the room was not locked. I left my two children there; the prisoner was a slight acquaintance of mine; he was taken up on the Wednesday with the coat on his back.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18250407-177-person947">
                  WILLIAM 
                  CAWTE
               <interp inst="t18250407-177-person947" type="surname" value="CAWTE"></interp>
